Also, India's biggest private company appears to be shifting the balance in=20
favor of an Iran pipeline. Reliance Industries Ltd., a Bombay-based polyeste=
r=20
and petroleum company that is gearing up to challenge government monopolies=20
in telecommunications and gas supply, recently launched a $10 million study=20
on importation of liquefied gas from Iran to India by ship, in partnership=20
with BP Inc. and National Iranian Oil Co. But industry officials familiar=20
with Reliance's plans said the company is expressing interest in the pipelin=
e=20
option, too, because of its cost advantages and potential to provide a backu=
p=20
energy source for Reliance's huge industrial complex in India's northwestern=
=20
Gujarat state.=20
