border, paying Pakistan's transit fees and guaranteeing safe passage through=
=20
Pakistan. Iran and Pakistan have warmed their previously frosty relations=20
recently, but whether Iran -- or even Pakistan itself -- could really=20
guarantee the pipeline's security is an open question. Matthew Forman, South=
=20
Asia specialist at the London-based consulting firm Control Risk Group, said=
=20
the pipeline would run through the huge and remote province of Baluchistan, =
a=20
lawless haven for smugglers where suspected tribal militants recently=20
