fabulous price from his viewpoint but bankrupts the customer is not a=20
fabulous deal at all but a bad one that invites political risk on top of=20
commercial risk.=20
The second and more important lesson is that state governments in India are=20
bankrupt but individuals and corporations are solvent. Enron made the seriou=
s=20
error of thinking it was easier to collect dues from a state government than=
=20
individual consumers.=20
