most solvent states. The Maharashtra State Electricity Board used to generat=
e=20
healthy profits in excess of Rs 100 crore per year.=20
The states fiscal deterioration in the last five years has not received the=20
attention it deserves. All states were hard hit by the Pay Commission award,=
=20
and most analysts (including me) blithely assumed that `good states like=20
Maharashtra would bounce back.=20
That optimism has turned out to be misplaced. Except for Gujarat, Tamil Nadu=
=20
and possibly one or two others, state governments today seem unable to meet=20
their commitments.=20
